President Uhuru Kenyatta was hosted for breakfast at ODM leader Raila Odinga's home in Bondo on Friday. Uhuru arrived in Kisumu on Thursday where he was given a hero's welcome. He is on a two-day working tour of Nyanza. Tycoon businessman Jimi Wanjigi attended the breakfast meeting. He went bearing gifts, which he presented to the hostess - Ida Odinga.  Raila Odinga and his wife Ida in Bondo on Friday, December 14, 2018. /COURTESY President Uhuru started his tour by launching the Universal Health Care pilot in Kisumu. UHC will be piloted in four counties: Kisumu, Nyeri, Machakos and Isiolo. After the breakfast at Raila's home, Uhuru is expected to preside over the Jaramogi Oginga Odinga University of Science and Technology graduation.  Jimi Wanjigi and Ida Odinga in Bondo on Friday, December 14, 2018. /COURTESY The university will confer honorary degrees on the President and Raila. Meanwhile, Deputy President William Ruto who accompanied the President to Kisumu on Thursday, was in Kisii on Friday. He presided over the Kisii University graduation. Click here for the latest political news  